The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

NATION BRIEFS

 Mumbai, Nov. 16 (PTI): Two persons were arrested for stealing diamonds worth Rs 4.5 crore from the house of a jeweller, even before a complaint was lodged.

 The two were picked up early this morning after they were seen showering money at a bar. They later confessed to have robbed diamonds. Pratap Zaveri, one of the owners of the Tribhuvandas Bhimji Zaveri jewellery shop chain lodged a complaint at 8 am after he found that loose diamonds went missing from his house while he was away.

 Ajmer (PTI): The management of the shrine of Sufi saint Khwaja Moinuddin Chisti has served showcause notices on actress Katrina Kaif and others for shooting a scene of the film Namaste London at the monument without its permission. Katrinas short dress during the shoot had angered a section of the management.

 Muzaffarnagar (PTI): Two brothers have been fined by a panchayat at a Uttar Pradesh village after their brides refused to marry them when the grooms family demanded dowry. Sisters Mohsina and Momina refused to marry Usman and Gulfam after their father allegedly demanded two cars in dowry just before the nikaah. The panchayat asked them to pay Rs 15,000 to the girls as compensation. 

 Mumbai (PTI): Extradited gangster Ejaz Pathan was beaten up by fellow prisoners at the Mumbai Central Jail in a clash with Dawood Ibrahim-group inmates. Pathan, a former Chhota Rajan associate, had allegedly abused the 1993 Bombay blasts accused.




